<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<!--
  Entitlements for the RaioPDF app binary and the Rust externalBin sidecars
  (raiopdf-engine-host, raiopdf-mcp-launcher), signed by Tauri with the
  hardened runtime enabled.

  Intentionally empty: the app itself needs nothing beyond hardened-runtime
  defaults. WKWebView's JavaScript JIT runs in Apple's out-of-process
  com.apple.WebKit.WebContent XPC service, which carries its own system
  entitlements - the host app does not need allow-jit for it. The Rust
  sidecars are plain native binaries with no JIT, no plugin loading, and no
  library injection.

  Runtime entitlements for the bundled payload interpreters live next to this
  file: jvm.entitlements (Temurin JRE) and node.entitlements (MCP Node
  runtime). Grant new entitlements here only with a proven necessity,
  documented in a comment.
-->
<dict/>
</plist>
